  "response": "To solve the expression \\( 6 + 1 \\times 0 + \\frac{2}{2} \\), we need to follow the order of operations (often remembered by the acronym PEMDAS/BODMAS: Parentheses/Brackets, Exponents/Orders, Multiplication and Division (from left to right), Addition and Subtraction (from left to right)).\n\n1. First, we perform the multiplication and division:\n   \\[\n   1 \\times 0 = 0\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   \\frac{2}{2} = 1\n   \\]\n\n2. Next, we substitute these results back into the expression:\n   \\[\n   6 + 0 + 1\n   \\]\n\n3. Now we perform the addition:\n   \\[\n   6 + 0 = 6\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   6 + 1 = 7\n   \\]\n\nSo, the final result is \\( 7 \\).",
